\begin_layout Standard
The rule-of-thumb for equipment costs is that the cost is 2 for d4, +1 per
 die-size, +1 per any Advantage without a balancing Disadvantage.
 Scope is relative to the Personal Scope for the campaign.
 E.g.
 at City Scope, Hardcase Armor is d6 vs.
 City Scope weapons, and would be scaled up or down vs.
 lower or higher Scopes.
 Similarly weapons, comm gear and the like all operate on a commensurate
 scale: a Vibro Knife at City Scope might well be able to slice through
 an ordinary automobile, while at Street scope it's a danger to pedestrians
 but not vehicles.
\end_layout

