 that has a Cost of 2 has a price in the tens of monetary units (credits,
 double-dollars, quatloos, what-have-you); a cost of 3 would be in the hundreds,
 and 4 would be in the thousands.
 Items that might Cost 1 aren't listed; they are free for practical purposes
 under most circumstances.
 Exact prices of items are assumed to vary according to quality and local
 circumstances; some might not even be available in a setting.
